{"questionId":"27695","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is defined as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mi>x</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup></math>, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.&nbsp;The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> is shown&nbsp;in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/59cd04b3eea0477c5eab86f9f8655149458d042d.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has a local maximum at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>. The graph intersects the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at the origin&nbsp;and at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the total area enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math>, the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis and the line <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61117</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p>area&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09885</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09885</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17527</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mn>0</mn><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09885</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></msubsup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>09885</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mi>d</mi><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>435901</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>17527</mn><mo>…</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61117</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p>area&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>61</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27695","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.3c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the total area enclosed by the graph of f, the x-axis and the line x=2.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.5—Integration introduction, areas between curve and x axis"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}